How to Run the Program:
Follow these steps to run the Adaptive Traffic Signal Control System on your local machine:

Prerequisites:
A modern web browser (e.g., Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, Microsoft Edge).
A code editor (e.g., Visual Studio Code) if you want to edit the code.
Basic knowledge of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (optional, for customization).

Steps to Run:
1. Clone or Download the Repository
Clone the repository using Git:
     git clone https://github.com/your-username/adaptive-traffic-signal.git
or download the ZIP file from GitHub and extract it to your desired directory.

2. Navigate to the Project Directory
Go to the project folder:
      cd adaptive-traffic-signal

3. Open the index.html File
Locate the index.html file in the project folder.

Double-click the file to open it in your default browser.

Alternatively, you can use a code editor:

Open the folder in Visual Studio Code.
Install the Live Server extension.
Right-click on the index.html file and select Open with Live Server.

4. Interact with the Application
Drag and drop video files into the upload containers or use the file input buttons to upload videos.
Click the Analyze Traffic button to trigger further actions (future development).
Notes:
This project is currently frontend-only. Traffic analysis is a placeholder for future enhancements.
For advanced features (e.g., video processing or backend functionality), you may need to set up a server and integrate AI/ML models.
